VERDICT: APPROVED_WITH_COMMENTS
The toast-to-inline notification migration is functionally implemented for the actual tool UIs, with no blocking regressions found.

Critical findings / analysis:
- The relevant tool pages that previously used popup toasts (rename, programcheat, ndagen, webscreen) now render inline message containers and route message rendering through those containers.
- The shared flash-message rendering in the base template was also changed from fixed-position popup style to inline page-level alerts, aligning with the stated goal.
- I did not find remaining toast-style notification logic in the reviewed tool templates; behavior now consistently presents in-page feedback with dismiss controls.
- Non-blocking concern: the working tree includes a very large set of unrelated `.local/skills` and `.local/secondary_skills` content changes/deletions. These are out of scope for the user-facing task and add merge risk/noise.

Security:
- None observed that are serious and task-blocking.

Next actions:
1) Before merge, isolate this PR to task-relevant app/template files only; drop unrelated `.local/*` churn from the commit.
2) Do a quick manual smoke test on all tool routes to confirm inline alerts appear in expected locations and dismiss/timeout behavior is acceptable.
3) If product intent is to keep messages visible until user action, remove auto-hide timers in a follow-up (current implementation still auto-dismisses).

